{{Infobox album | name = What Do You Want from Live | type = Live | artist = [[The Tubes]] | cover = WhatDoYouWantFromLive.png | alt = | released = February, 1978 | recorded = November, 1977 | venue = | studio = | genre = [[Rock music|Rock]], [[experimental rock]], [[progressive rock]] | length = 72:42 | label = [[A&M Records|A&M]] | producer = Pete Henderson, Rikki Farr | prev_title = [[Now (The Tubes)|Now]] | prev_year = 1977 | next_title = [[Remote Control (The Tubes album)|Remote Control]] | next_year = 1979 }} {{Album ratings | rev1 = [[AllMusic]] | rev1Score = {{Rating|3|5}} <ref name="Guarisco">{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r51554|first=Donald A.|last=Guarisco}}</ref> | rev2 = | rev2Score = }} '''''What Do You Want from Live''''' is the fourth album released by [[The Tubes]]. It is a [[live album]], recorded at the [[Hammersmith Odeon]], London.
== Background == The Tubes toured the UK at the height of the [[punk rock]] era in 1977. Despite their somewhat out-of-step musicality, the band's humorous and manic stage show found favor all over the country. The cabaret-like shows lasted over an hour, ending with Waybill – in character as "Quay Lewd", a parody of a drug-addled rock star – getting crushed to death by a giant stack of (fake) speakers. ''[[NME]]'' pronounced the tour a great success, writing: "They came, they outraged, they conquered."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.loudersound.com/features/the-tubes-they-came-they-outraged-they-conquered|title=The Tubes: They came, they outraged, they conquered |first=Mark |last=Blake |date=August 29, 2016 |website=[[Loudersound.com]] |accessdate=August 31, 2019 }}</ref>
