==Personnel== *[[Fee Waybill]] - vocals *[[Bill Spooner]] - guitar, vocals *Michael Cotten - synthesizer *[[Mingo Lewis]] - drums, percussion *[[Prairie Prince]] - drums *Roger Steen - guitar *[[Vince Welnick]] - keyboards *Rick Anderson - bass *Re Styles - vocals
== Critical reception == Although [[AllMusic]] reviews the album very favorably, describing it as "witty and entertaining" throughout, it ultimately gives it three stars out of five because the audio portion of the show is simply unable to convey the full impact of a Tubes concert in their heyday. "The downside of ''What Do You Want from Live''", says reviewer Donald A. Guarisco, "is that some of the numbers are less potent without the choreographed routines surrounding them{{nbsp}}... this leaves the listener feeling like they're only witnessing part of the joke", adding wistfully, "if only someone would put out a video of one of the Tubes' shows from this era."<ref name="Guarisco"/>
